#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/marketplace/traction-eos/references/process.md
M|references|Most companies have processes. Few have them documented. Even fewer have them followed consistently. The Process Component fixes this by identifying your handful of core processes, documenting them si
M|references|You do not need to doc every procedure in your company. That leads to thousand-page manuals nobody reads. Instead, doc the 20% of your processes that drive 80% of your results.
M|references|**What this means in practice:**
M|references|- Identify 5-7 core processes (not 50)
M|references|- doc each process in 5-20 major steps (not 200)
M|references|- Add just enough detail so someone competent can follow it (not a manual for someone with zero ctx)
M|references|| Too Little | Just Right | Too Much |
M|references||-----------|------------|----------|
M|references|| "Handle customer complaints" | 8 steps from complaint received to resolution confirmed, with key dec points noted | 47-page complaint handling manual with scripts for every scenario |
M|references|| No one knows the process | New hires can follow it in their first week | No one reads the documentation |
M|references|| Inconsistent execution | 80%+ consistency across the team | Rigid process that cannot adapt |
M|references|Every company, regardless of industry, has a set of core processes that define how the business runs. Most companies have 5-7 core processes.
M|references|| Process | What It Covers | Who Owns It |
M|references||---------|---------------|-------------|
M|references|| **HR Process** | Hiring, onboarding, performance reviews, offboarding | Head of People / Integrator |
M|references|| **Sales Process** | Lead qualification through close and handoff | Head of Sales |
M|references|| **mkt Process** | Lead generation, nurturing, and conversion to sales-ready leads | Head of mkt |
M|references|| **Operations/Delivery Process** | How you produce and deliver your product or service | Head of Operations |
M|references|| **Customer Retention Process** | Onboarding, support, renewals, upsells | Head of Customer Success |
M|references|| **fin Process** | Invoicing, collections, reporting, budgeting | Head of fin |
M|references|| **Product/Engineering Process** | Ideation, dev, QA, dpl | Head of Product/Engineering |
M|references|Ask your leadership team:
M|references|1. "What are the major processes that run our business?"
M|references|2. "If a new leadership team took over tomorrow, what processes would they need to understand to run the company?"
M|references|3. "Where does inconsistency cause the most problems for customers or employees?"
M|references|List everything mentioned, then consolidate into 5-7 core processes. Each should span a meaningful arc of work (lead to close, not just "make a phone call").
M|references|Every core process follows the same documentation structure. Keep it simple. The goal is clarity, not comprehensiveness.
M|references|```
M|references|Process Name: _________________________ (give it a branded name)
M|references|Owner: _________________________
M|references|Last Updated: _________________________
M|references|Version: _________________________
M|references|Purpose: One sentence describing what this process achieves.
M|references|Steps:
M|references|1. [Step Name]
M|references|- Key details or substeps
M|references|- dec point or criteria
M|references|2. [Step Name]
M|references|- Key details or substeps
M|references|3. [Step Name]
M|references|...
M|references|```
M|references|Give each process a memorable, branded name. This makes it easier for the team to reference and creates a sense of identity around how you work.
M|references|**Examples:**
M|references|- Sales Process: "The Closer" or "The Revenue Engine"
M|references|- Onboarding Process: "The Welcome Track" or "First 30 Days"
M|references|- Support Process: "The Resolution Path" or "Care Loop"
M|references|- Delivery Process: "The Build Cycle" or "Ship It"
M|references|**Owner:** VP of Sales
M|references|**Purpose:** Convert qualified leads into paying customers through a consistent, repeatable process.
M|references|| Step | Action | Key Details | Exit Criteria |
M|references||------|--------|-------------|--------------|
M|references|| 1 | **Qualify Lead** | Apply BANT criteria (Budget, Authority, Need, Timeline). Score 1-4. | Score of 3+ moves forward |
M|references|| 2 | **Discovery Call** | 30-minute structured call using question guide. Uncover 3 core pain points. | Pain points documented, next step agreed |
M|references|| 3 | **Demo** | Customized to prospect's pain points. Show, don't tell. 45 minutes max. | Prospect confirms fit |
M|references|| 4 | **Proposal** | Send within 24 hours of demo. Include 3 options (good/better/best). | Proposal delivered and receipt confirmed |
M|references|| 5 | **Follow Up** | 3 touches in 7 days: email (day 1), call (day 3), email (day 7). | dec received |
M|references|| 6 | **Close** | Signed agreement and payment terms confirmed. | Contract signed |
M|references|| 7 | **Handoff** | Introduce customer to onboarding team. Complete handoff doc. | Onboarding team confirms receipt |
M|references|**Owner:** VP of Operations
M|references|**Purpose:** Deliver projects on time, on budget, and at the quality standard promised.
M|references|| Step | Action | Key Details | Exit Criteria |
M|references||------|--------|-------------|--------------|
M|references|| 1 | **Kickoff** | Internal kickoff within 48 hours of signed contract. rv scope, timeline, team. | All team members clear on deliverables |
M|references|| 2 | **Planning** | Create project plan with milestones. Identify risks. | Plan ap by project sponsor |
M|references|| 3 | **Execution** | Weekly status updates. Flag blockers within 24 hours. | Milestones met on schedule |
M|references|| 4 | **Quality Check** | Internal rv before any deliverable goes to client. | Passes quality checklist |
M|references|| 5 | **Client rv** | Present deliverable. Collect feedback. | Client ap or revision list |
M|references|| 6 | **Revisions** | Address feedback within 3 business days. One round included. | Revisions ap |
M|references|| 7 | **Close Out** | Final delivery, documentation, lessons learned, satisfaction survey. | Survey score 4+/5 |
M|references|**Owner:** Head of People / Integrator
M|references|**Purpose:** Attract, hire, develop, and retain people who are the right people in the right seats.
M|references|| Step | Action | Key Details | Exit Criteria |
M|references||------|--------|-------------|--------------|
M|references|| 1 | **Job Definition** | Write Accountability Chart seat description with core values requirements. | ap by hiring manager and Integrator |
M|references|| 2 | **Source** | Post on 3+ channels. Employee referral bonus active. | 10+ qualified applicants |
M|references|| 3 | **Screen** | Phone screen (15 min) for core values and basic qualifications. | 5 candidates advance |
M|references|| 4 | **Interview** | Two rounds: core values interview (behavioral), skills interview (tec). | 2-3 finalists |
M|references|| 5 | **People Analyzer** | Score each finalist on core values and GWC. | All "+" on values, all "Y" on GWC |
M|references|| 6 | **Offer** | Extend offer within 48 hours of final interview. | Offer accepted |
M|references|| 7 | **Onboard** | 90-day onboarding plan: Week 1 orientation, 30/60/90 check-ins. | 90-day rv passed |
M|references|| 8 | **Develop** | Quarterly conversations using core values and GWC framework. | Ongoing |
M|references|**Owner:** Head of Customer Success
M|references|**Purpose:** Resolve customer issues quickly and use feedback to improve the product and service.
M|references|| Step | Action | Key Details | Exit Criteria |
M|references||------|--------|-------------|--------------|
M|references|| 1 | **Receive** | Ticket created via email, chat, or phone. Auto-acknowledge within 1 hour. | Ticket logged in system |
M|references|| 2 | **Triage** | Classify severity (P1-P4). Assign to appropriate team member. | Assigned within 2 hours |
M|references|| 3 | **Investigate** | Reproduce the issue. Check knw base. Consult engineering if needed. | Root cause identified |
M|references|| 4 | **Resolve** | Implement fix or workaround. Communicate resolution to customer. | Customer confirms resolution |
M|references|| 5 | **Follow Up** | Check in 48 hours later. Confirm issue has not recurred. | Customer satisfied |
M|references|| 6 | **doc** | Update knw base if new issue type. Flag product bugs for engineering. | KB updated |
M|references|| 7 | **Report** | Weekly metrics: volume, resolution time, CSAT, recurring issues. | Scorecard updated |
M|references|**Owner:** Head of fin / Controller
M|references|**Purpose:** Manage the company's financial health through timely invoicing, accurate reporting, and proactive cash management.
M|references|| Step | Action | Key Details | Exit Criteria |
M|references||------|--------|-------------|--------------|
M|references|| 1 | **Invoice** | gen invoice within 24 hours of deliverable/milestone. | Invoice sent and confirmed |
M|references|| 2 | **Track** | Monitor payment status weekly. Flag AR over 30 days. | AR report updated |
M|references|| 3 | **Collect** | Follow up on overdue invoices: email at 31 days, call at 45 days, escalate at 60 days. | Payment received or escalated |
M|references|| 4 | **Report** | Weekly flash report (revenue, expenses, cash). Monthly P&L. | Reports delivered on schedule |
M|references|| 5 | **Forecast** | Quarterly cash flow forecast. Annual budget rv. | Forecast ap by leadership |
M|references|Documented processes are worthless if nobody follows them. FBA (Followed By All) is the implementation framework that turns documentation into habit.
M|references|```
M|references|doc → Train → Measure → Update → Repeat
M|references|```
M|references|**Step 1: doc** (covered above)
M|references|**Step 2: Train**
M|references|- Every employee involved in a process receives training on the documented steps
M|references|- Training is not a 2-hour lecture. It is hands-on practice with feedback.
M|references|- New hires are trained on relevant processes in their first two weeks
M|references|**Step 3: Measure**
M|references|- Spot-check compliance monthly (rv 5-10 random instances of the process)
M|references|- Track process-related quality metrics on the Scorecard
M|references|- Ask: "Is the process being followed? If not, why?"
M|references|**Step 4: Update**
M|references|- Processes should be rv quarterly
M|references|- If the team consistently deviates from a step, either enforce it or update it
M|references|- The person who owns the process owns the updates
M|references|| Question | Yes/No | Action if No |
M|references||----------|--------|-------------|
M|references|| Is the process documented and accessible? | | Write/share it |
M|references|| Has everyone been trained on it? | | Schedule training |
M|references|| Are we measuring compliance? | | Add spot-checks |
M|references|| Is the process producing consistent results? | | Identify which step is failing |
M|references|| Has it been rv in the past quarter? | | Schedule rv |
M|references|Processes are easier to follow when they are visual. Use these approaches:
M|references|```
M|references|[Lead Received] → [Qualify (BANT)] → Score 3+?
M|references|├── Yes → [Discovery Call]
M|references|└── No  → [Nurture Sequence]
M|references|```
M|references|Use swimlanes when multiple people or departments are involved:
M|references|| mkt | Sales | Operations |
M|references||-----------|-------|------------|
M|references|| gen lead | | |
M|references|| Qualify MQL | | |
M|references|| | Accept SQL | |
M|references|| | Discovery call | |
M|references|| | Close deal | |
M|references|| | | Kick off project |
M|references|| | | Deliver |
M|references|For processes with many parallel tasks (like onboarding), a checklist works better than a flowchart:
M|references|**New Employee Onboarding Checklist**
M|references|- [ ] Equipment ordered (IT, day -7)
M|references|- [ ] Accounts created (IT, day -3)
M|references|- [ ] Welcome email sent (HR, day -1)
M|references|- [ ] Office tour (Manager, day 1)
M|references|- [ ] Core values training (HR, day 1)
M|references|- [ ] Process training begins (Manager, day 2)
M|references|- [ ] 30-day check-in scheduled (Manager, day 1)
M|references|1. **See:** New hire observes an experienced team member performing the process
M|references|2. **Do:** New hire performs the process with the experienced team member coaching
M|references|3. **Teach:** New hire explains the process back to someone else
M|references|If they can teach it, they know it. This method works for any process in any department.
M|references|| Week | Focus | Method | Assessment |
M|references||------|-------|--------|------------|
M|references|| 1 | Company overview, core values, core processes overview | Orientation sessions | Can state core values and name all core processes |
M|references|| 2 | Primary process (the one they will use daily) | See-Do-Teach | Completes process independently with <2 errors |
M|references|| 3 | Secondary processes (ones they interact with) | See + documentation rv | Can explain how their work connects to upstream/downstream processes |
M|references|| 4 | Edge cases and exceptions | Scenario-based practice | Handles 3 of 4 edge case scenarios correctly |
M|references|Every quarter, each process owner reviews their core process:
M|references|1. **Compliance check (10 min):** Are people following the process? Where are the deviations?
M|references|2. **Results check (10 min):** Is the process producing the desired outcomes? What do the Scorecard metrics say?
M|references|3. **Improvement check (10 min):** What feedback have we received? What steps should be added, removed, or changed?
M|references|| Process | Compliance Rate | Outcome Quality | Last Updated | Status |
M|references||---------|---------------|-----------------|-------------|--------|
M|references|| The Revenue Engine | 85% | Win rate 28% | Jan 15 | Healthy |
M|references|| The Build Cycle | 70% | On-time 82% | Dec 1 | Needs attention |
M|references|| The People Path | 90% | 90-day retention 95% | Jan 20 | Healthy |
M|references|| The Care Loop | 60% | CSAT 3.8/5 | Oct 15 | At risk |
M|references|| The Money Flow | 95% | AR <30 days 92% | Jan 10 | Healthy |
M|references|Any process below 80% compliance or with declining outcome quality goes to the Issues List for IDS.